U.S. 30-Year Treasuries Rise, Paring Yesterday’s Biggest Drop Since 2008

-- B y   N a o t o   H o s o d a
-- 
2011-08-12T00:20:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/u-s-30-year-treasuries-rise-paring-yesterday-s-biggest-drop-since-2008.html
Thirty-year Treasuries advanced,
paring some of yesterday’s loss. The 30-year yield fell two
basis points to 3.75 percent as of 9:15 a.m. in  Tokyo . The yield
surged 25 basis points yesterday in  New York  after climbing as
much as 29 basis points, the most on an intraday basis since
2008.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Naoto Hosoda at 
 nhosoda@bloomberg.net  